parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause sudden loss of acceleration, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. In some cases, metal shreds from the failed bearing can spread throughout the transmission system, making repair impossible and necessitating a costly replacement.
symptoms: Sudden failure to accelerate
hard shifting
trouble code P1870 indicating internal slippage
transmission gasket failure
and repeated transmission failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to safety risks, inconvenience, and potential damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reading fluctuates erratically
the fuel gauge shows an incorrect reading
the fuel gauge suddenly drops to empty
the fuel gauge jumps back up to full after dropping to empty
the vehicle runs out of fuel despite the gauge showing a full tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts to repair the fuel filler valve recall can lead to delays and inconvenience for the vehicle owner, potentially causing safety risks if the recall is not addressed promptly.
symptoms: Dealership does not have parts available to repair the fuel filler valve recall
delays in repair
inconvenience to the vehicle owner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A coolant leak can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant leaking from the engine
engine overheating
temperature gauge rising
engine stalling or shutting down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty oxygen sensors can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to decreased fuel efficiency, engine performance issues, and potential engine damage.
symptoms: Check engine light comes on
decreased fuel efficiency
engine performance issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or shut down can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine shuts down without warning
loss of steering and brake control
check engine light comes on
vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side cargo door hinges can cause the door to freeze, making it difficult or impossible to open, which can lead to inconvenience, damage, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The side cargo door is stuck and cannot be opened
the door is difficult to open
the door freezes at the hinges.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Gust Locks on Side Doors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of gust locks on the side doors can cause the doors to close unexpectedly, potentially trapping or injuring passengers' legs or ankles.
symptoms: The side doors close on passengers' legs or ankles
the doors do not stay open
the doors do not have a mechanism to hold them open.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Air Unit Corrosion and Compressor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear air unit connections and compressor failure can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to a lack of cold air and reduced vehicle comfort.
symptoms: The air conditioning system does not blow cold air
corrosion is visible on the rear air unit connections
the compressor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Plastic Stem in Heating/Cooling Unit
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic stem in the heating/cooling unit can cause the control knobs for the air conditioner and heater to break, leading to a loss of functionality and reduced vehicle comfort.
symptoms: The control knobs for the air conditioner and heater break
the plastic stem inside the heating/cooling unit splits
the metal rod from the unit is exposed.
